      <section eId="sec_76_300">
        <num>76.300</num>
        <content>
          <p>The county judge/executive of any county in which a metropolitan sewer district has been established, upon petition of twenty-five percent (25%) of the resident freeholders therein may establish a sewer construction district for the purpose of providing sewers and/or drainage facilities to serve the district. The petition shall describe the territory intended to be included in the district, and the sewer and drainage conditions and facilities existing in this territory.</p>
